t%2C%20a%20ball%20and%20their%20rackets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sense%20of%20loss%20was%20devised%20out%20of%20life%20and%20its%20absence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EWestern%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ELane%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%20a%20short%20novel%20on%20squash%20and%20loss.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20362px)%2085vw%2C%20362px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F16044445%2F91sfG7t2wL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22362%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F16044445%2F91sfG7t2wL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20621w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F16044445%2F91sfG7t2wL._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-186x300.jpg%20186w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689409%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22583%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Western%20Lane%2C%E2%80%99%20Chetna%20Maroo%2C%20Picador%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20stupendous%20work%20of%20literature%2C%20loss%20thrives%20in%20all%20the%20spaces%20outside%20and%20inside%20a%20squash%20court.%20It%20echoes%20%E2%80%93%20at%20once%2C%20louder%20and%20quieter%20%E2%80%93%20with%20every%20strike%20at%20the%20ball.%20And%20it%20fills%20all%20gaps.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChetna%20Maroo%E2%80%99s%20world%20in%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebookerprizes.com%2Fthe-booker-library%2Fauthors%2Fchetna-maroo%5C%22%3EBooker%20Shortlisted%20novel%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20squeezed%20out%20of%20a%20family%20of%20four%20somewhere%20unnamed%20in%20England%20%E2%80%93%20Pa%2C%20Mona%2C%20Kush%20and%20Gopi.%20The%20three%20girls%20are%20between%2015%20and%2011%20years%20old.%20Their%20mother%2C%20Charu%2C%20is%20newly%20dead%20in%20the%20novel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20space%20left%20by%20Charu%20enters%20the%20sport%20of%20squash%2C%20played%20by%20Gopi%2C%20who%20narrates%20the%20book.%20Gopi%20develops%20a%20romantic%20friendship%20with%20Ged.%20Ged%E2%80%99s%20mother%20runs%20the%20bar%20above%20the%20squash%20court%2C%20Western%20Lane.%20Uncle%20Pavan%20is%20a%20calm%20and%20tortured%20person.%20Aunt%20Ranjan%20is%20severe%20but%20also%20quiet%20and%20conservative.%20Maqsud%20is%20Pakistani%20and%20clearly%20the%20local%20squash%20advisor%E2%80%A6%20The%20book%20has%20very%20few%20characters%20and%20most%20dance%20around%20the%20sport%2C%20doing%20very%20little%20and%20mostly%20observing%20things%20in%20their%20own%20time.%20Men%2C%20women%2C%20boys%20and%20girls%20are%20remembered%20with%20sighs%2C%20minuscule%20gestures%20and%20the%20shortest%20of%20sentences.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20result%20is%20startling%20and%20sweeping.%20It%20pushes%20the%20reader%20into%20herself%2C%20pulls%20a%20blanket%20over%20her%20and%20over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20mere%20160%20pages%2C%20almost%20chastens%20her.%20You%20emerge%20from%20the%20book%20thinking%20that%20everything%20that%20is%20not%20the%20bare%20and%20unspoken%20truth%20is%20immaterial%20to%20life%20and%20existence.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhich%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20the%20book%20has%20no%20frivolity%20or%20fun.%20Mona%2C%20Kush%20and%20Gopi%20are%20young%20girls%2C%20after%20all.%20But%20the%20book%20does%20them%20a%20giant%20service%20the%20way%20women%20writers%20writing%20girls%20can%20and%20often%20have.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20instance%2C%20it%20not%20only%20takes%20Gopi%E2%80%99s%20fierce%20understanding%20of%20squash%20seriously%2C%20it%20offers%20significant%20space%20to%20her%20to%20allow%20her%20to%20express%20her%20personal%20philosophy%20of%20the%20sport.%20What%20does%20it%20feel%20like%20to%20be%20alone%20in%20the%20T%20of%20the%20court%3F%20How%20do%20players%20think%20of%20throwaway%20advice%20on%20their%20game%3F%20There%20is%20a%20holiness%20associated%20with%20hearing%20sportspersons%20talk%20of%20their%20internal%20compulsions%20while%20playing%20%E2%80%93%20Maroo%20accords%20it%20all%20to%20her%20young%20protagonist.%20She%20raises%20her%20love%20for%20squash%20to%20a%20holy%20plane%2C%20positing%20as%20her%20inspiration%20one%20of%20the%20greatest%20in%20the%20sport%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DBc7BoBFpdvw%5C%22%3Ereal-life%20Pakistani%20hero%20Jahangir%20Khan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%20one%20allows%20young%20girls%20to%20speak%20this%20way%20%E2%80%93%20to%20have%20a%20sacred%20sense%20of%20seriousness%20over%20a%20world%20like%20sports%20which%20is%20quite%20abundantly%20occupied%20by%20men.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20book%20respects%20the%20unshorn%20grit%20that%20girls%20have%2C%20and%20also%20that%20essential%20teenage%20experience%20%E2%80%93%20of%20that%20gigantic%20internal%20churn%20when%20society%2C%20family%20and%20you%20yourself%20are%20pulling%20yourself%20in%20different%20directions.%20Here%20too%2C%20brevity%20is%20beautiful.%20With%20the%20overarching%20tool%20of%20grief%2C%20Maroo%20delves%20into%20that%20liminal%20state%20and%20offers%20the%20reader%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20revelation.%20Her%20technique%20is%20so%20sharp%20that%20it%20strikes%20you%20as%20otherworldly%20in%20a%20world%20of%20novels%20dealing%20in%20fantasy%20or%20sharp%20realism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20a%20work%20of%20words%2C%20this%20story%20of%20an%20immigrant%20Gujarati%20Jain%20family%20has%20a%20lot%20of%20silences.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMaroo%E2%80%99s%20readers%20are%20sure%20to%20be%20familiar%20with%20the%20shattering%20quiet%20that%20occupies%20houses%20after%20deaths.%20But%20they%2