unis%2C%20according%20to%20an%20AFP%20journalist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20news%20update%2C%20Al%20Jazeera%20said%20Al-Dahdouh%20was%20able%20to%20leave%20the%20area%20of%20the%20strike%20to%20look%20for%20help%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20by%20the%20time%20he%20reached%20an%20ambulance%2C%20medics%20said%20they%20could%20not%20return%20to%20the%20site%20of%20the%20attack%20because%20it%20was%20too%20dangerous.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20army%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20an%20AFP%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20'A%20compassionate%20soul'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAl%20Jazeera%20managing%20editor%20Mohamed%20Moawad%20paid%20tribute%20to%20Abu%20Daqqa%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20saying%3A%20%26quot%3BHis%20unwavering%20commitment%20to%20truth%20and%20storytelling%20has%20left%20an%20indelible%20mark%20on%20our%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSamer%2C%20whose%20lens%20captured%20the%20raw%20and%20unfiltered%20reality%20of%20life%20in%20Gaza%2C%20was%20not%20just%20a%20skilled%20professional%20but%20a%20compassionate%20soul%20who%20understood%20the%20power%20of%20visual%20storytelling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20pursuit%20of%20truth%2C%20our%20cameraman%20faced%20immense%20risks%20to%20bring%20viewers%20a%20deeper%20understanding%20of%20the%20human%20experience%20in%20Gaza%2C%26quot%3B%20Moawad%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Foreign%20Press%20Association%20called%20on%20the%20Israeli%20army%20to%20investigate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20consider%20this%20a%20grave%20blow%20to%20the%20already%20limited%20freedom%20of%20the%20press%20in%20Gaza%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Hamas%20operative%20group%2C%20a%20first%20strike%20had%20targeted%20a%20school%20belonging%20to%20the%20UN%20agency%20for%20Palestinian%20refugees%20in%20Khan%20Yunis%2C%20which%20the%20journalists%20had%20come%20to%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20second%20strike%20then%20took%20place%20which%20%26quot%3Bdeliberately%20targeted%20the%20journalists%26quot%3B%2C%20Hamas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20%26quot%3Battempt%20to%20intimidate%20journalists%20so%20that%20they%20do%20not%20document%20the%20(Israeli)%20massacres%20committed%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%26quot%3B%2C%20Hamas%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAl%20Jazeera%20said%20it%20held%20%26quot%3BIsrael%20accountable%20for%20systematically%20targeting%20and%20killing%20Al%20Jazeera%20journalists%20and%20their%20families%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20National%20Security%20Council%20spokesman%20John%20Kirby%20told%20a%20press%20briefing%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe%20still%20don't%20have%20any%20indications%26quot%3B%20that%20Israel%20is%20%26quot%3Bdeliberately%20going%20after%20journalists%20trying%20to%20cover%20this%20war%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20October%2C%20emotional%20footage%20showed%20Al-Dahdouh%20learning%20on%20camera%20that%20his%20wife%20and%20two%20children%20were%20killed%20by%20an%20Israeli%20strike%20on%20the%20Nuseirat%20refugee%20camp%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2060%20journalists%20and%20media%20staff%20have%20died%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war%20between%20Hamas%20and%20Israel%20on%20October%207%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20began%20after%20Hamas%20launched%20an%20unprecedented%20attack%20on%20Israel%20from%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20on%20October%207%20that%20Israeli%20officials%20say%20killed%20around%201%2C200%20people%2C%20mostly%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVowing%20to%20destroy%20Hamas%20and%20bring%20home%20an%20estimated%20250%20hostages%20abducted%20by%20operatives%20to%20Gaza%2C%20Israel%20launched%20a%20massive%20offensive%20that%20has%20left%20much%20of%20the%20besieged%20territory%20in%20ruins.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hamas%20government%20says%20the%20war%20has%20killed%20a