%20may%20be%20different%20from%20dogs%2C%20who%20are%20mainly%20focused%20on%20the%20social%20bond%20with%20their%20owner%20rather%20than%20the%20object%2C%20Jemma%20Forman%2C%20an%20animal%20psychologist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Sussex%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20via%20email.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20cats%2C%20we%20are%20not%20so%20sure%20whether%20fetching%20is%20a%20social%20bonding%20activity%20for%20them%20or%20whether%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20get%20us%20to%20simply%20throw%20an%20object%20for%20their%20entertainment%20or%20perhaps%20both%2C%26quot%3B%20Forman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForman%20and%20other%20researchers%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Dbef6a8ea990429927777b58427940f7084a601c040c0c46e1fb49d957f3afa1a%26postID%3D657c9c048d7dad6fbf2a1a2d%26postSlug%3Dcats-play-fetch-research-toys-mice-2023-12%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41598-023-47409-w%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20paper%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20Scientific%20Reports%20on%20cats%20that%20play%20fetch.%20They%20surveyed%20hundreds%20of%20owners%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20the%20playful%20behavior%20in%20over%201%2C000%20cats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESome%20cats%20like%20to%20fetch%20toys%2C%20hair%20ties%2C%20and%20tinfoil%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20researchers%20asked%20cat%20owners%20what%20objects%20their%20pets%20like%20to%20fetch.%20Toys%20topped%20the%20list%2C%20including%20plushies%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fpets%2Fbest-cat-toy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecatnip%20toys%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20fake%20mice%2C%20Forman%20said.%20Cats%20also%20seemed%20to%20like%20to%20play%20with%20crumpled%20paper%20or%20tinfoil%2C%20hair%20ties%2C%20cotton%20pads%2C%20and%20bobby%20pins%2C%20Forman%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20overall%20it's%20objects%20that%20cats%20can%20opportunistically%20play%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20Forman%20said%2C%20so%20small%2C%20light-weight%20items%20they%20can%20carry%20in%20their%20mouths%20without%20swallowing.%20(Rubber%20bands%20and%20hair%20ties%20can%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-york-north-yorkshire-66912737%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eespecially%20dangerous%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fthings-you-should-never-do-to-a-cat-2020-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecats%20to%20swallow%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Forman%2C%20the%20most%20surprising%20thing%20the%20survey%20revealed%20was%20that%20almost%20all%20the%20respondents%2C%20about%2094%25%2C%20said%20their%20cat%20wasn't%20trained%20to%20play%20the%20game.%20%26quot%3BIt%20shows%20that%20more%20cats%20have%20the%20capability%20to%20play%20fetch%20than%20perhaps%20previously%20thought%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20some%20owners%20found%20out%20their%20cat%20enjoys%20fetch%20simply%20by%20accident.%20Like%20if%20their%20cat%20retrieved%20a%20piece%20of%20paper%20that%20missed%20the%20trash%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFor%20cats%2C%20playing%20is%20similar%20to%20hunting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20exactly%20why%20cats%20enjoy%20playing%20fetch%20will%20take%20further%20research%2C%20Froman%20said%20most%20cats%20play%20similarly%20to%20how%20they%20hunt%3A%20chasing%2C%20leaping%2C%20biting%2C%20stalking%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20owners%20said%20their%20cats%20would%20play%20with%20their%20toys%20for%20a%20bit%20before%20bringing%20them%20back.%20%26quot%3BSo%20throwing%20the%20object%20could%20be%20mimicking%20the%20motion%20of%20fast-moving%20prey%20that%20motivates%20the%20cat%20to%20chase%20after%20it%20and%20play%20with%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Forman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22youtube%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FueQTmB76M1k%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22A%20cat%20fetching%20a%20tinfoil%20ball.%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20finding%20that%20likely%20won't%20surprise%20many%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudies-about-why-cats-make-good-pets-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecat%20owners%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20felines%20were%20generally%20the%20ones%20setting%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMore%20owners%20reported%20that%20their%20cats%20are%20in%20control%20of%20initiating%20their%20fetching%20sessions%20than%20they%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Forman%20said.%20Cats%20were%20also%20more%20enthusiastic%20or%20played%20longer%20when%20they%20initiated%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20don't%20be%20offended%20if%20your%20cat%20doesn't%20chase%20its%20toy%20when%20you%20decide%20to%20toss%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForman%20said%20playing%20with%20cats%20could%20help%20owners%20understand%20their%20pets'%20behaviors.%20%26quot%3BUnderstanding%20the%20needs%20of%20your%20cat%20and%20improving%20owner%20understanding%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmiss-ex-boyfriend-cats-more-than-him-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecat%20communication%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20key%20to%20engaging%20in%20a%20positive%20play%20session%20and%20ensuring%20future%20positive%20play%20sessions%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20the%20survey%20targeted%20people%20with%20cats%20who%20play%20fetch%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20how%20common%20the%20behavior%20is.%20That%20could%20be%20an%20area%20of%20future%20research%2C%20Forman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOwners%20with%20fetching%20cats%20can%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funiversityo