0it%20calls%20Active%20Listening.%20CMG%20claimed%20that%20its%20technology%20can%20use%20microphone%20data%20from%20devices%20like%20smartphones%20and%20tablets%2C%20specifically%20analyzing%20%26quot%3Bpre-purchase%20conversations.%26quot%3B%20The%20since-deleted%20blog%20post%20also%20mentions%20using%20AI%20to%20determine%20when%20the%20phrases%20heard%20from%20smart%20devices%20could%20be%20%26quot%3Brelevant%26quot%3B%20to%20advertisers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20Cox%20Media%20Group's%20overview%20of%20Active%20Listening.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657ca8750ec98e92f7501a1d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECox%20Media%20Group%20wrote%20about%20Active%20Listening%20in%20a%20deleted%20blog%20post%2C%20writing%20%26quot%3BImagine%20a%20world%20where%20you%20can%20read%20minds.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blog%20post%20discussing%20Active%20Listening%20has%20since%20been%20deleted%20from%20CMG's%20website%20%E2%80%94%20trying%20to%20access%20the%20page%20on%20Friday%20just%20took%20you%20back%20to%20CMG's%20home%20page.%20However%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20231214235444%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmglocalsolutions.com%2Fblog%2Factive-listening-an-overview%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earchived%20version%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20post%20is%20still%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECMG%20described%20Active%20Listening%20as%20%26quot%3Ba%20world%20where%20no%20pre-purchased%20murmurs%20go%20unanalyzed%2C%26quot%3B%20telling%20advertisers%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20whispers%20of%20consumers%20become%20a%20tool%20for%20you%20to%20target.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20said%20in%20the%20blog%20post%20that%20its%20Active%20Listening%20is%20legal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20what%20you're%20thinking.%20Is%20this%20even%20legal%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20post%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20legal%20for%20phones%20and%20devices%20to%20listen%20to%20you.%20When%20a%20new%20app%20download%20or%20update%20prompts%20consumers%20with%20a%20multi-page%20term%20of%20use%20agreement%20somewhere%20in%20the%20fine%20print%2C%20Active%20Listening%20is%20often%20included.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222498%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20of%20Cox%20Media%20Group's%20FAQ%20section%20on%20Active%20Listening.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657ca7eb0ec98e92f75019b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221561%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20screenshot%20from%20Cox%20Media%20Group's%20since-deleted%20blog%20post%20on%20%26quot%3BActive%20Listening.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EActive%20Listening%20uses%20voice%20data%20from%20conversations%20that%20users%20have%2C%20according%20to%20CMG.%20This%20is%20possible%20thanks%20to%20AI%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bgrowing%20ability%20to%20access%20microphone%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECMG%20also%20said%20it%20can%20set%20certain%20terms%20as%20keywords%20for%20advertisers%20that%20could%20relate%20to%20different%20items%20or%20services%20they%20are%20trying%20to%20sell.%20This%20would%20enable%20advertisers%20to%20target%20customers%20based%20on%20who%20might%20have%20used%20these%20keywords.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20this%20unprecedented%20understanding%20of%20consumer%20behavior%2C%20we%20can%20deliver%20personalized%20ads%20that%20make%20your%20target%20audience%20think%3A%20wow%2C%20they%20must%20be%20a%20mind%20reader%2C%26quot%3B%20CMG%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20important%20to%20note%20that%20it's%20not%20clear%20whether%20this%20technology%20and%20marketing%20is%20actually%20happening.%20Cox%20Media%20Group%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20request%20for%20comment%20ahead%20of%20publication.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20marketing%20claims%20won't%20help%20with%20larger%20privacy%20fears%20around%20devices%20with%20microphones%20in%20them.%20Some%20people%20have%20long%20claimed%20without%20evidence%20that%20apps%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fdoes-facebook-listen-to-you%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20listen%20to%20your%20conversations%20to%20serve%20you%20better%20ads%20(Facebook%20has%20long%20denied%20this%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20app%20only%20uses%20your%20microphone%20with%20permission%20and%20when%20you%20are%20using%20a%20feature%20that%20would%20require%20a%20microphone%2C%20like%20recording%20audio%20or%20video).%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20there%20is%20a%20way%20to%20disable%20Facebook%20and%20Instagram's%20access%20to%20your%20smartphone%20mic.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EApple%20has%20changed%20in%20recent%20years%20to%20its%20iOS%20software%20to%20force%20app-makers%20to%20be%20more%20transparent%20when%20an%20app%20is%20accessing%20or%20using%20your%20device's%20microphone%20or%20location%20data.%20Your%20iPhone%20also%20shows%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fgreen-orange-light-dot-on-iphonehttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fgreen-orange-light-dot-on-iphone%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorange%20dot%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20top-right%20corner%20of%20the%20screen%20when%20your%20phone's%20microphone%20is%20in%20use%2C%20like%20during%20a%20phone%20call.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcox-active-listening-claims-conversations-phones-target-ads-12-2023%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702671754000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657c951f0ec98e92f7500b85%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcox-active-listening-claims-conversa