%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F62df15a9d571050018ad7acd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222848%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETwain%20was%20engaged%20with%20scientists%2C%20responding%20to%20their%20calls%2C%20for%20a%20jaw-dropping%2020-minutes.%20%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20sailed%20a%20boat%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-saved-money-living-in-alaska-as-a-teacher-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlaska%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20played%20what's%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bcontact%20call%26quot%3B%20into%20the%20ocean%20to%20see%20if%20any%20whales%20would%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EContact%20calls%20are%20similar%20to%20a%20human%20greeting.%20Whales%20use%20them%20to%20call%20over%20other%20whales%20or%20let%20each%20other%20know%20where%20they%20are%2C%20lead%20author%20Brenda%20McCowan%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20UC%20Davis's%20School%20of%20Veterinary%20Medicine%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20are%20one%20of%20the%20most%20common%20signals%20within%20the%20humpback%20whale%20social%20sound%20repertoire%2C%26quot%3B%20Fred%20Sharpe%2C%20co-author%20and%20principal%20investigator%20with%20the%20Alaska%20Whale%20Foundation%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESure%20enough%2C%20Twain%20swam%20up%20to%20the%20boat%20and%20circled%20it.%20For%20the%20next%2020%20minutes%2C%20the%20scientists%20emitted%20the%20same%20contact%20call%2036%20different%20times%20at%20varying%20intervals%2C%20and%20Twain%20responded%20to%20the%20call%20each%20time%2C%20even%20closely%20matching%20the%20intervals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeaning%2C%20if%20the%20scientists%20waited%2010%20seconds%20before%20playing%20a%20call%20back%20to%20Twain%2C%20she%20would%20in%20turn%20wait%2010%20seconds%20before%20responding%2C%20McCowan%20said.%20This%20type%20of%20interval%20matching%20suggests%20Twain%20was%20engaged%20in%20an%20intentional%20exchange%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20certainly%20felt%20like%20we%20had%20been%20heard%2C%26quot%3B%20Sharpe%20told%20BI%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20their%20work%20is%20done%20with%20a%20permit%20from%20the%20National%20Marine%20Fisheries%20Service%20and%20readers%20should%20not%20try%20this%20at%20home%20(or%20sea).%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20hope%20that%20she%20felt%20the%20same%20way%2C%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20this%20is%20the%20first%20such%20communicative%20exchange%20between%20humans%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Ftags%2Fhumpback%2Bwhales%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehumpback%20whales%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20humpback%20'language%2C'%26quot%3B%20McCowan%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.seti.org%2Fpress-release%2Fwhale-seti-groundbreaking-encounter-humpback-whales-reveals-potential-non-human-intelligence%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Estatement%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20calls%20came%20from%20humpback%20whales%20the%20researchers%20had%20recorded%20from%20a%20small%20group%20of%20whales%20just%20the%20day%20before%20their%20encounter.%20The%20group%20had%20included%20Twain%2C%20so%20it's%20possible%20Twain%20was%20responding%20to%20her%20own%20signal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20might've%20been%20playing%20back%20her%20own%20hello%20to%20her%2C%26quot%3B%20Sharpe%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what%20does%20this%20have%20to%20do%20with%20talking%20to%20aliens%3F%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurns%20out%2C%20Twain's%20behavior%20could%20be%20akin%20to%20how%20intelligent%20alien%20races%20may%20seek%20humanity%20out%2C%20said%20Laurance%20Doyle%2C%20a%20principal%20investigator%20at%20the%20SETI%20Institute%20and%20coauthor%20on%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECommunicating%20with%20extraterrestrials%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222464%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Amy%20Adams%20as%20Louise%20Banks%20communicating%20with%20aliens%20in%20%26quot%3BArrival.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6544c4cbb788914e554f6f7e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221310%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmy%20Adams%20as%20Louise%20Banks%20communicating%20with%20aliens%20in%20%26quot%3BArrival.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EParamount%20Pictures%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20important%20assumption%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falien-signals-search-for-extraterrestrial-intelligence-study-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esearch%20for%20extraterrestrial%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20that%20extraterrestrials%20will%20be%20interested%20in%20making%20contact%20and%20so%20target%20human%20receivers%2C%26quot%3B%20sort%20of%20like%20how%20Twain%20responded%20to%20the%20contact%20call%20from%20the%20scientists%2C%20Doyle%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDoyle%20and%20his%20colleagues%20at%20SETI%20are%20working%20with%20whale%20and%20animal%20experts%20at%20UC%20Davis%20and%20the%20Alaska%20Whale%20Foundation%20to%20create%20intelligent%20filters%20to%20aid%20in%20their%20search%20for%20extraterrestrial%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20extraterrestrials%20are%20out%20there%2C%20sending%20us%20signals%2C%20trying%20to%20communicate%2C%20we%20might%20miss%20them%20if%20we%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20look%20for%2C%20Doyle%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20perfecting%20these%20intelligent%20filters%2C%20scientists%20could%20use%20them%20to%20identify%20intelligent%20signals%20from%20space%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20make%20first%20contact%20with%20an%20alien%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20diverse%20intelligences%20on%20this%20planet%2C%20and%20by%20studying%20them%2C%20we%20can%20better%20understand%20what%20an%20alien%20intelligence%20might%20be%20like%2C%20because%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20be%20exactly%20like%2