rmer%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20chief%20minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%20on%20Friday%20wrote%20to%20state%20Chief%20Justice%20Ravi%20Malimath%20seeking%20forgiveness%20for%20two%20ABVP%20functionaries%20who%20were%20arrested%20for%20taking%20the%20car%20of%20a%20judge%20to%20ferry%20an%20ailing%20person%20to%20a%20hospital%20in%20Gwalior.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20AVP's%20Gwalior%20secretary%20Himanshu%20Shrotriya%20(22)%20and%20deputy%20secretary%20Sukrit%20Sharma%20(24)%20were%20arrested%20on%20Monday%20under%20the%20MP%20Dakaiti%20Aur%20Vyapharan%20Prabhavit%20Kshetra%20Adhiniyam%20(MPDVPK%20Act)%2C%20an%20anti-dacoity%20law%2C%20after%20they%20snatched%20the%20car's%20key%20from%20its%20driver%20at%20Gwalior%20railway%20station%20and%20took%20Ranjeet%20Singh%2C%20VC%20of%20a%20private%20university%20in%20Jhansi%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20to%20hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETheir%20bail%20was%20rejected%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20they%20are%20in%20judicial%20custody%20at%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20it%20is%20a%20different%20sort%20of%20crime%20committed%20for%20a%20holy%20cause%20and%20done%20on%20humanitarian%20ground%20for%20saving%20life%2C%20it%20is%20worth%20forgiving.%20The%20intention%20of%20Himanshu%20Shrotriya%20(22)%20and%20Sukrit%20Sharma%20(24)%20was%20not%20to%20commit%20crime.%20So%20keeping%20in%20view%20their%20future%20they%20should%20be%20forgiven%2C%26quot%3B%20Chouhan%20wrote%20in%20the%20letter%20to%20Justice%20Malimath.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20denying%20them%20bail%2C%20the%20special%20judge%20for%20dacoity%20cases%20Sanjay%20Goyal%20had%20observed%20that%20one%20seeks%20help%20with%20politeness%20and%20not%20with%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%2C%20citing%20the%20police%20diary%20in%20the%20incident%2C%20said%20an%20ambulance%2C%20which%20is%20the%20ideal%20vehicle%20for%20such%20purposes%2C%20had%20arrived%20to%20ferry%20the%20ailing%20man.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20speaking%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20Sand