leged%20plot%20to%20kill%20Khalistani%20terrorist%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%20had%20been%20detained%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20the%20government%20of%20the%20Czech%20Republic%20has%20told%20NDTV.%20Nikhil%20Gupta%20was%20detained%20at%20the%20Prague%20airport%20in%20June%20and%2C%20the%20Czech%20government%20said%2C%20the%20US%20had%20submitted%20an%20extradition%20request%20two%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResponding%20to%20a%20series%20of%20queries%20sent%20by%20NDTV%2C%20the%20Czech%20Republic's%20Ministry%20of%20Justice%20said%20the%20extradition%20had%20been%20requested%20for%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20%26quot%3Bmurder%20for%20hire%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Ministry%20of%20Justice%20of%20the%20Czech%20Republic%20can%20confirm%20that%20Mr.%20Nikhil%20Gupta%20was%20apprehended%20and%20afterwards%20taken%20into%20provisional%20custody%20in%20the%20Czech%20Republic%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20competent%20authority%20of%20the%20USA%2C%20which%20subsequently%20submitted%20the%20request%20for%20extradition%20of%20Mr%20Gupta%20to%20the%20USA%20in%20August%202023.%20The%20extradition%20of%20Mr%20Gupta%20was%20requested%20for%20the%20crime%20of%20conspiracy%20to%20commit%20murder%20for%20hire%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20said%20the%20Municipal%20Public%20Prosecution%20Office%20in%20Prague%20conducted%20a%20preliminary%20investigation%20and%20then%20filed%20a%20motion%20to%20declare%20the%20extradition%20admissible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUpon%20this%20motion%2C%20the%20Municipal%20Court%20in%20Prague%20ruled%20that%20the%20extradition%20of%20Mr.%20Gupta%20to%20the%20USA%20is%20admissible.%20However%2C%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20Municipal%20Court%20in%20Prague%20is%20not%20yet%20in%20legal%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20a%20question%20on%20access%20to%20Czech%20court%20records%2C%20the%20ministry%20said%20the%20decisions%20of%20courts%20are%20not%20publicly%20available%20online.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%20has%20charged%20Mr%20Gupta%20with%20conspiring%20with%20an%20Indian%20government%20official%20to%20assassinate%20Pannun%20on%20American%20soil.%20The%20Khalistani%20terrorists%20holds%20citizenship%20of%20both%20the%20US%20and%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gupta%2C%2052%2C%20is%20accused%20of%20attempting%20to%20hire%20a%20hitman%2C%20who%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20an%20undercover%20US%20federal%20agent.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20their%20indictment%2C%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20have%20addressed%20the%20Indian%20official%20as%20%26quot%3BCC-1%26quot%3B%20and%20claimed%20he%20masterminded%20the%20plot%20from%20India%20to%20eliminate%20%26quot%3Ban%20attorney%20and%20political%20activist%20who%20is%20a%20US%20citizen%20of%20Indian%20origin%20residing%20in%20New%20York%20City%26quot%3B.%20If%20convicted%2C%20Mr%20Gupta%2C%20faces%20up%20to%2020%20years%20in%20prison.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESupreme%20Court%20Hearing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Gupta%20moved%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Friday%2C%20through%20a%20family%20member%20identified%20only%20as%20Mr%20X%2C%20and%20claimed%20multiple%20violations%20of%20fundamental%20rights.%20In%20his%20petition%2C%20he%20has%20also%20requested%20the%20Indian%20government%20to%20intervene%20in%20his%20extradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20SVN%20Bhatti%20termed%20the%20matter%20an%20%26quot%3Bextremely%20sensitive%20issue%20for%20the%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%26quot%3B%20and%20told%20senior%20advocate%20CA%20Sundaram%2C%20representing%20Mr%20Gupta%2C%20to%20approach%20a%20court%20in%20the%20Czech%20Republic%2C%20according%20to%20news%20agency%20PTI.%20The%20court%20said%20it%20will%20take%20up%20the%20matter%20on%20January%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702654440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2