%20minister%20Thomas%20Isaac%20and%20Kerala%20Infrastructure%20Investment%20Fund%20Board%20(KIIFB)%20officials%20regarding%20the%20Masala%20Bonds%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMasala%20bonds%20are%20rupee-denominated%20bonds%20issued%20in%20foreign%20markets%2C%20allowing%20Indian%20entities%20to%20raise%20funds%20from%20international%20investors.%20These%20bonds%20are%20an%20instrument%20for%20Indian%20companies%20to%20tap%20into%20global%20capital%20markets%20without%20exposing%20themselves%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20currency%20fluctuations%20since%20the%20issuance%20is%20in%20Indian%20Rupees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20both%20KIIFB%20and%20Isaac%20had%20moved%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20summons%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20in%20relation%20to%20its%20probe%20into%20the%20alleged%20violations%20of%20the%20Foreign%20Exchange%20Management%20Act%20(FEMA)%20in%20the%20issuance%20of%20%E2%80%98Masala%20Bonds%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0petition%C2%A0moved%20by%20Isaac%20challenged%20the%20summons%20issued%20by%20the%20ED%20seeking%20his%20personal%20documents%20as%20well%20as%20those%20of%20his%20family%20members%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20same%20probe%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fmasala-bonds-kerala-high-court-ed-will-withdraw-summons-thomas-isaac-kiifb%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20the%20KIIFB%20challenged%20the%20repeated%20issuance%20of%20summons%20by%20the%20ED%20to%20KIIFB%20officers%2C%20including%20its%20CEO%2C%20K.M.%20Abraham%2C%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20confirmed%20to%20the%20high%20court%20that%20it%20had%20issued%20a%20Non-Objection%20Certificate%20(NOC)%20to%20the%20KIIFB%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Exchange%20Management%20Act%20(FEMA)%20for%20raising%20funds%20through%20masala%20bonds%20abroad.%3C%2Fp%3E%