gathers%20pace.%20The%20answer%2C%20alarmingly%2C%20is%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUAE%3A%20controversial%20hosts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20year%E2%80%99s%20talks%20were%20controversial%20from%20the%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20role%20of%20oil%20man%20Sultan%20Al%20Jaber%20as%20COP28%20president%20fuelled%20concerns%20about%20the%20hosting%20role%20of%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20%E2%80%93%20a%20country%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcop28-inside-the-united-arab-emirates-the-oil-giant-hosting-2023-climate-change-summit-217859%5C%22%3Esignificant%20interests%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20sustaining%20a%20fossil%20fuel%20economy.%20Then%20came%20reports%20Al%20Jaber%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F03%2Fback-into-caves-cop28-president-dismisses-phase-out-of-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3Ehad%20questioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20scientific%20rationale%20for%20phasing%20out%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20tackle%20climate%20change%2C%20amid%20reports%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20trade%20negotiations%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fscience-environment-67508331%5C%22%3Esidelines%20of%20negotiations%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20this%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fscience-environment-67607289%5C%22%3Eunprecedented%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20lobbyists%20and%20geoengineering%20advocates%20attended%20the%20talks.%20This%20did%20not%20create%20the%20ideal%20conditions%20for%20action%20on%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Loss%20and%20damane%E2%80%99%20breakthrough%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20their%20credit%2C%20the%20organisers%20had%20an%20early%20win%20with%20an%20agreement%20to%20establish%20a%20%E2%80%9Closs%20and%20damage%E2%80%9D%20fund%20whereby%20richer%20nations%20compensate%20poorer%20nations%20for%20the%20effects%20of%20climate%20change.%20The%20creation%20of%20this%20fund%20is%20one%20of%20the%20big%20outcomes%20of%20the%20talks.%20It%E2%80%99s%20taken%20a%20long%20time%20to%20get%20here%2C%20after%20initially%20being%20suggested%20by%20Vanuatu%20in%201991%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fcop27-one-big-breakthrough-but-ultimately-an-inadequate-response-to-the-climate-crisis-194056%5C%22%3Esupported%20in%20principle%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20talks%20in%20Egypt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20it%20needed%3F%20Because%20developing%20states%20are%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20damage%20done%20by%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20have%20limited%20ability%20to%20meet%20the%20cost%20of%20repair%20and%20rebuilding.%20The%20fund%20also%20points%20to%20the%20particular%20obligations%20of%20developed%20states%20and%20significant%20emitters%20who%20have%20largely%20caused%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20still%20big%20questions%20about%20the%20measure%20%E2%80%93%20most%20importantly%2C%20how%20well%20it%20will%20be%20funded.%20Despite%20the%20fanfare%2C%20just%20US%24700%20million%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F06%2F700m-pledged-to-loss-and-damage-fund-cop28-covers-less-than-02-percent-needed%5C%22%3Ehas%20been%20committed%3C%2Fa%3E%20so%20far%20to%20the%20fund%20aimed%20at%20compensating%20states%20for%20damage%20that%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets-global.website-files.com%2F605869242b205050a0579e87%2F655b50e163c953059360564d_L%2526DC_L%2526D_Package_for_COP28_20112023_1227.pdf%5C%22%3Erecent%20estimates%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20already%20runs%20into%20the%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20per%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20concerns%20over%20having%20the%20fund%20administrated%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20which%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fnov%2F29%2Fwhy-loss-and-damage-funds-are-key-to-climate-justice-for-developing-countries-at-cop28%5C%22%3Equestionable%3C%2Fa%3E%20environmental%20credentials%20and%20a%20patchy%20record%20on%20transparency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20fund%20itself%20is%20an%20admission%20of%20failure.%20It%E2%80%99s%20needed%20only%20because%20the%20international%20community%20has%20failed%20to%20stop%20climate%20change%20from%20happening%2C%20and%20is%20unlikely%20to%20prevent%20it%20reaching%20dangerous%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDeckchairs%20on%20the%20Titanic%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20talks%20went%20on%2C%20they%20got%20harder.%20The%20tricky%20topic%3A%20fossil%20fuels.%20It%20may%20amaze%20outsiders%2C%20but%20this%2C%20the%2028th%20annual%20climate%20talks%2C%20is%20the%20first%20time%20nations%20have%20directly%20addressed%20phasing%20out%20fossil%20fuels.%20Last%20year%2C%20nations%20agreed%20to%20accelerate%20the%20exit%20from%20coal%20%E2%80%93%20the%20dirtiest%20fuel%20%E2%80%93%20but%20said%20nothing%20of%20gas%20or%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20days%2C%20debate%20raged%20over%20whether%20to%20apply%20phrases%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Cphasing%20out%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cphasing%20down%E2%80%9D%20or%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cunabated%E2%80%9D%20to%20fossil%20fuels.%20Even%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Ccould%E2%80%9D%20became%20controversial%2C%20when%20tied%20to%20the%20suggestion%20countries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fsustainability%2Fclimate-energy%2Fcop28-presidency-wants-historic-mention-fossil-fuels-text-up-nations-2023-12-12%5C%22%3Emight%20consider%3C%2Fa%3E%20limiting%20fossil%20fuel%20production%20and%20consumption.%20To%20victims%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20the%20arguments%20might%20look%20like%20rearranging%20deckchairs%20on%20the%20Titanic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20nations%20were%20prepared%20to%20acknowledge%20the%20need%20to%20eliminate%20fossil%20fuels.%20Others%20noted%20the%20need%20for%20a%20future%20transition%20without%20compromising%20their%20need%20to%20develop%20or%20earn%20export%20income.%20Still%20others%20suggested%20the%20effects%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20might%20be%20minimised%20through%20technologies%20such%20as%20carbon%20capture%20and%20storage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20198%20participating%20countries%20needed%20to%20approve%20any%20final%20declaration.%20So%20you%20can%20see%20the%20difficulty%20in%20reaching%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20100%20countries%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F12%2F12%2Fclimate%2Fcop28-climate-summit-agreement-tuesday%2Findex.html%5C%22%3Ehave%20pushed%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20global%20commitment%20to%20a%20total%20phase-out%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20But%20nations%20that%20profit%20immensely%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20Russia%2C%20Iran%2C%20Iraq%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2Flive%2F2023%2Fdec%2F11%2Fcop28-live-time-to-be-ambitious-says-president-as-summit-enters-final-days%5C%22%3Eopposed%3C%2Fa%3E%20any%20mention%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20the%20final%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20draft%20of%20the%20declaration%20did%20not%20go%20down%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHost%20negotiators%20attempted%20to%20broker%20a%20deal%20between%20the%20competing%20interests%20by%20omitting%20any%20reference%20to%20phasing%20%E2%80%9Cout%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cdown%E2%80%9D.%20Instead%2C%20they%20suggested%20countries%20%E2%80%9Ccould%E2%80%9D%20consider%20reducing%20production%20and%20consumption%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20The%20compromise%20text%20produced%20by%20COP28%20president%20Al%20Jaber%20and%20his%20team%20seemed%20to%20err%20on%20the%20side%20of%20fossil%20fuel%20interests.%20Despite%20this%2C%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20backers%20were%20still%20opposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutcry%20was%20swift%20from%20advocates%20for%20strong%20climate%20action.%20The%20draft%20was%20labelled%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdeath%20certificate%E2%80%9D%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F12%2Fcop-28-australia-us-and-uk-say-they-wont-sign-agreement-that-would-be-death-certificate-for-small-islands%5C%22%3Evulnerable%20small%20island%20states%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20a%20%3Ca%3Ewithering%20attack%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20from%20concerned%20states%2C%20NGOs%20and%20even%20states%20with%20patchier%20climate%20records%20such%20as%20Australia%2C%20the%20United%20States%2C%20Canada%20and%20Japan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20agreement%20%E2%80%93%20but%20is%20it%20enough%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20talks%20extended%20well%20beyond%20the%20original%20deadline%2C%20it%20came%20as%20some%20surprise%20that%20the%20final%20document%20was%20endorsed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Flive%2Fworld-67674841%5C%22%3Erelatively%20swiftly%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20version%20was%20more%20strident%20on%20the%20contribution%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20some%20advocates%20saw%20this%20as%20a%20significant%20signal.%20It%20asserted%20that%20the%20transition%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20needed%20to%20take%20place%20quickly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F13%2Fcop28-landmark-deal-agreed-to-transition-away-from-fossil-fuels%5C%22%3Ethough%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20just%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%20manner%2C%20accelerating%20action%20in%20this%20critical%20decade%2C%20so%20as%20to%20achieve%20net%20zero%20by%202050%20in%20keeping%20with%20the%20science%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20says%20something%20about%20the%20glacial%20pace%20of%20climate%20talks%20since%20they%20began%20in%201992%20that%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20contribution%20of%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20climate%20change%20has%20ever%20been%20acknowledged%20in%20a%20final%20COP%20document.%20And%20here%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fdec%2F12%2Fwhy-implementation-matters-in-the-global-fight-again-the-climate-crisis%5C%22%3Ecritics%20lamented%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20lack%20of%20detail%20over%20how%20goals%20would%20be%20implemented%20or%20commitments%20realised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conference%20also%20delivered%20important%20commitments%20to%20tripling%20renewable%20energy%2C%20expanding%20nuclear%20power%2C%20and%20a%20new%20pledge%20to%20cut%20emissions%20from%20cooling%20technologies%20such%20as%20air%20conditioning%2C%20which%20will%20become%20increasingly%20important%20as%20the%20world%20heats%20up.%20The%20talks%20also%20saw%20recognition%20of%20the%20increasingly%20significant%20role%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cop28.com%2Fen%2Ffood-and-agriculture%5C%22%3Eagricultural%20sector%20in%20contributing%20to%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20more%20must%20be%20done.%20In%202023%2C%20temperatures%20are%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fe360.yale.edu%2Fdigest%2F1.5-degrees-scientific-consensus%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DOn%2520a%2520monthly%2520scale%252C%2520it%2Cexpected%2520to%2520surpass%25201.5%2520degrees.%5C%22%3Espiking%20past%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20crucial%20threshold%20of%201.5%C2%B0C.%20The%20global%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Funs-global-stocktake-on-climate-offers-a-sobering-emissions-reckoning-but-there-are-also-signs-of-progress-217093%5C%22%3Estocktake%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20emissions%20cuts%20released%20in%20advance%20of%20the%20talks%20shows%20our%20current%20efforts%20are%20not%20enough%20to%20stop%20further%20warming.%20Countries%20such%20as%20Australia%20advocated%20stronger%20language%20on%20ending%20fossil%20fuels%20while%20maintaining%20a%20steady%20pipeline%20of%20new%20fossil%20fuel%20projects%20at%20home.%20It%E2%80%99s%20little%20wonder%2C%20then%2C%20that%20the%20lead%20negotiator%20of%20the%20the%20Alliance%20of%20Small%20Island%20States%20said%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22ht