high%20court%20judges%20appointed%20between%202018%20and%20earlier%20this%20month%20are%20upper-caste%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsansad.in%2FgetFile%2Fannex%2F262%2FAU1390.pdf%3Fsource%3Dpqars%5C%22%3EUnion%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20Thursday%20(December%2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeghwal%20was%20answering%20a%20question%20by%20BJP%20MP%20from%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Harnath%20Singh%20Yadav%20asking%20if%20there%20were%20caste-based%20reservations%20for%20the%20appointment%20of%20judges%20to%20high%20courts%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20response%20said%20that%20492%20out%20of%20650%20judges%20appointed%20to%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20high%20courts%20between%202018%20and%20December%206%20were%20upper-caste%20(76%25)%2C%2077%20were%20OBCs%20(12%25)%2C%2036%20were%20minorities%20(6%25)%2C%2020%20were%20SCs%20(3%25)%2C%2012%20were%20STs%20(2%25)%20and%2013%20judges%20were%20of%20unknown%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20was%20provided%20by%20the%20judges%20who%20had%20been%20recommended%20for%20appointment%2C%20Meghwal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20clarified%20that%20there%20were%20no%20caste-based%20reservations%20for%20the%20appointment%20of%20high%20court%20and%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%2C%20but%20reiterated%20his%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20stance%20that%20it%20has%20been%20requesting%20high%20court%20chief%20justices%20to%20give%20%E2%80%9Cdue%20consideration%E2%80%9D%20to%20candidates%20from%20marginalised%20backgrounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20he%20provided%20on%20Thursday%20were%20slightly%20different%20from%20the%20ones%20he%20provided%20on%20December%207%20while%20answering%20a%20question%20in%20the%20same%20House%20by%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20MP%20from%20Kerala%2C%20John%20Brittas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsansad.in%2FgetFile%2Fannex%2F262%2FAU598.pdf%3Fsource%3Dpqars%5C%22%3EIn%20that%20response%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Meghwal%20said%20that%20out%20of%20650%20judges%20appointed%20to%20the%20high%20courts%20between%202018%20and%20December%202%2C%2023%20were%20SC%20(compared%20to%20the%20more%20recent%20figure%20of%2020)%2C%20ten%20were%20ST%20(as%20opposed%20to%2012)%20and%2076%20were%20OBC%20(as%20opposed%20to%2077).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeghwal%20also%20provided%20information%20on%20the%20number%20of%20women%20judges%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20courts.%20According%20to%20his%20reply%2C%20three%20judges%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20of%20December%202%20were%20women%2C%20as%20were%20108%20judges%20across%20all%20high%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20the%20total%20number%20of%20high%20court%20judges%20as%20per%20Meghwal%E2%80%99s%20latest%20response%20as%20790%2C%20the%20proportion%20of%20women%20judges%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20high%20courts%20stands%20at%20roughly%2014%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20trying%20to%20gain%20control%20over%20judicial%20appointments%20by%20doing%20away%20with%20the%20collegium%20system%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20maintained%20that%20in%20the%20three%20decades%20since%20the%20system%20has%20been%20in%20place%2C%20it%20has%20failed%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsocial-diversity-missing-in-higher-judiciary-centre-tells-house-panel%2Farticleshow%2F96838669.cms%5C%22%3Esocial%20diversity%20in%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20as%20originally%20devised%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20parliamentary%20panel%20said%20in%20August%20this%20year%20that%20a%20provision%20to%20appoint%20adequate%20numbers%20of%20women%2C%20OBC%2C%20SC%20and%20ST%20candidates%20as%20judges%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20be%20clearly%20mentioned%20in%20the%20Memoranda%20of%20Procedure%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20under%20finalisation%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fparliamentary-panel-says-provision-to-ensure-representation-in-higher-judiciary-should-be-mentioned-in-mop%2Farticle67169709.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20panel%20added%20that%20the%20representation%20of%20these%20groups%20in%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20was%20%E2%80%9Cfar%20below%20the%20desired%20levels%20and%20does%20not%20reflect%20the%20social%20diversity%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudges%20are%20appointed%20to%20the%20high%20courts%20and%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20as%20per%20as%20the%20procedure%20laid%20down%20in%20the%20memorandum%20of%20procedure%20(MoP)%2C%20Meghwal%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20response%20to%20Brittas%20stated%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20agreed%20in%20a%20draft%20MoP%20that%20while%20%E2%80%9Cmerit%20and%20integrity%E2%80%9D%20would%20primarily%20decide%20the%20appointment%20of%20high%20court%20judges%2C%20the%20representation%20of%20women%20and%20candidates%20from%20marginalised%20communities%20would%20be%20given%20%E2%80%9Cas%20far%20as%20possible%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20law%20minister%20said%20that%20while%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20acknowledged%20the%20need%20to%20revisit%20the%20MoP%20and%20that%20the%20government%20has%20recommended%20improvements%20to%20it%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20views%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20draft%20MoP%20are%20awaited%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20the%20top%20court%20has%20pushed%20back%20on%20the%20criticism%20of%20the%20collegium%20system%2C%20admitting%20that%20though%20the%20system%20may%20not%20be%20perfect%2C%20it%20is%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcollegium-system-supreme-court-centre-law-of-land%5C%22%3Elaw%20of%20the%20land%20and%20must%20be%20followed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702626128000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15124522%2Fpexels-sora-shimazaki-5668473.jpg%2